            <div corresp="#c0850f2">
                <head>Riga, Latvia.</head>
                <p>David B. Macgowan, Consul Cl. 6, lately designed to Vladivostok was detailed to
                    Riga Aug. 21, 1922; appt Consul, Class 5, Mar. 1, 1923; Consul class 4 June 5,
                    1924. Appt'd also a Secretary in the Diplomatic Service and assigned to Riga,
                    etc. as First Secretary Nov. 5, 1927.</p>
                <p>"Charles H. Heisler, lately F.S.O, Unclassified and V.C., was appt'd F.S.O, class
                    8, also Consul Aug. 8, 1924, as designed to Malmo Sept. 17, 1924</p>
                <p>Earl L. Packer, lately F.S.O., Unclassified, and V.C. was appt'd F.S.O, class 8
                    Feb. 24, 1925. Also Consul Mar. 8, 1925. Detailed to Dept. of State Feb. 6,
                    1925.</p>
                <p>Alger &amp; Carleton detailed to Dept. of State, temp., Sept. 7, 1932.</p>
                <p>A. Dana Hodgdon detailed to " " " " , Sept. 17, 1935.</p>
